   "body" : "It looks like banlist.dat is only actually created if nodes are banned. Otherwise, this will appear on every start:\r\n```\r\n2016-02-01 09:55:14 ERROR: Read: Failed to open file /home//.bitcoin/banlist.dat\r\n2016-02-01 09:55:14 Invalid or missing banlist.dat; recreating\r\n```\r\n- The `ERROR:` makes it look like a serious issue\r\n- It's probably best to just create the file there. But at the very least, the log message shouldn't promise to do something it isn't going to do\r\n",
